'''Phil Eason''' ([[May 5]], [[1960s|1960]]<ref name="FT" />&ndash;[[April 5]], [[2021]])<ref name="Twitter" /> was a British actor who played [[Yaddle/Legends|Yaddle]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']].<ref name="FT" />

An experienced puppeteer with many credits on TV commercials and series, he is mainly remembered for his puppets in [[Wikipedia:Little Shop of Horrors (1986 film)|''Little Shop of Horrors'']], [[Wikipedia:Labyrinth (film)|''Labyrinth'']], [[Wikipedia:The NeverEnding Story III|''The NeverEnding Story III'']], [[Wikipedia:Muppet Treasure Island|''Muppet Treasure Island'']], and [[Wikipedia:Lost in Space (film)|''Lost in Space'']].

He also appeared as a Human actor in ''Diabolical Properties'' and ''New Adventures of Pinocchio'', but returned to puppet work in [[1999]] for both George Orwell's [[Wikipedia:Animal Farm|''Animal Farm'']] and [[George Lucas]]' [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], where he puppets Jedi Master Yaddle. Yaddle does not appear in any further movies, nor was Eason called again to play a different character.

Since then, Eason was voice actor and puppeteer for the two first Harry Potter movies ([[Wikipedia:Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (film)|''Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone'']], [[2001]]; and [[Wikipedia:Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets (film)|''Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets'']], [[2002]]), and for [[Wikipedia:The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (film)|''The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy'']].

